WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.671 --> 00:00:03.338
(ambient music)

00:00:10.640 --> 00:00:13.760
- The logic behind the creation of X3

00:00:13.760 --> 00:00:15.330
has to do with the fact

00:00:15.330 --> 00:00:18.250
that you are seven times stronger

00:00:18.250 --> 00:00:19.413
than you know you are.

00:00:20.590 --> 00:00:23.970
That's based on biomechanics
and variable resistance.

00:00:23.970 --> 00:00:24.920
Let me show you.

00:00:24.920 --> 00:00:27.720
Right here, you are seven times stronger

00:00:27.720 --> 00:00:30.550
than you are right here.

00:00:30.550 --> 00:00:33.230
The curve is not linear in the middle.

00:00:33.230 --> 00:00:37.190
Therefore, we change the weight with X3

00:00:37.190 --> 00:00:39.930
so that we hold the
lighter weight back here

00:00:39.930 --> 00:00:41.600
where the joints are compromised

00:00:41.600 --> 00:00:43.120
and more likely to injure,

00:00:43.120 --> 00:00:46.680
and we hold a very
powerful weight out here

00:00:46.680 --> 00:00:50.180
where you are capable
of producing that force.

00:00:50.180 --> 00:00:53.670
This means that you
get a much deeper level

00:00:53.670 --> 00:00:57.080
of fatigue, and with that
deeper level of fatigue

00:00:57.080 --> 00:01:00.520
comes a more aggressive rate of growth.

00:01:00.520 --> 00:01:03.810
People can put on 20 pounds
of muscle in six months.

00:01:03.810 --> 00:01:05.610
We've seen that with many

00:01:05.610 --> 00:01:07.870
of the tens of thousands of users.

00:01:07.870 --> 00:01:11.030
The problem with lifting regular weights

00:01:11.030 --> 00:01:15.770
is we don't get that seven-fold stimulus,

00:01:15.770 --> 00:01:18.910
the possibility of triggering more growth,

00:01:18.910 --> 00:01:21.670
by handling force appropriate

00:01:21.670 --> 00:01:23.480
to the range of motion we're in.

00:01:23.480 --> 00:01:27.573
For example, when you're
lifting a regular weight,

00:01:28.520 --> 00:01:30.960
you pick the weight that you can handle

00:01:30.960 --> 00:01:33.133
back here in your weakest position.

00:01:34.050 --> 00:01:35.930
When you're in your strongest position,

00:01:35.930 --> 00:01:37.923
you're hardly using any muscle at all.

00:01:39.070 --> 00:01:42.580
That's when the most muscle
is capable of firing.

00:01:42.580 --> 00:01:46.153
You're really only training
your weakest position,

00:01:46.990 --> 00:01:49.250
which doesn't mean it doesn't translate

00:01:49.250 --> 00:01:51.670
into strength in the
stronger range of motion,

00:01:51.670 --> 00:01:54.030
but it does mean you're
firing the least amount

00:01:54.030 --> 00:01:56.670
of tissue possible and
taking the least amount

00:01:56.670 --> 00:02:00.583
of tissue to fatigue in that experience.

00:02:01.760 --> 00:02:05.150
There are some companies
that are trying to draft

00:02:05.150 --> 00:02:06.270
off of our success

00:02:06.270 --> 00:02:08.960
by selling just bands by themselves.

00:02:08.960 --> 00:02:12.080
The problem is you have two choices.

00:02:12.080 --> 00:02:14.120
You have a very light-weight band,

00:02:14.120 --> 00:02:17.210
which is kinda like a
rehab-type of weight,

00:02:17.210 --> 00:02:18.840
20 pounds or something like that.

00:02:18.840 --> 00:02:20.773
That's not gonna stimulate any growth.

00:02:22.560 --> 00:02:25.070
When I do a chest press with this bar,

00:02:25.070 --> 00:02:28.633
I'm over 500 pounds at
peak; 540, actually.

00:02:30.720 --> 00:02:33.270
When somebody trains with just bands,

00:02:33.270 --> 00:02:34.500
they're either going too light,

00:02:34.500 --> 00:02:37.300
or if they try and use
a heavier set of bands,

00:02:37.300 --> 00:02:41.213
this happens, because the
band wants to be a circle.

00:02:42.350 --> 00:02:45.260
It doesn't have the bar to
conform to a straight line,

00:02:45.260 --> 00:02:48.510
which we interface with
straight and flat very well.

00:02:48.510 --> 00:02:50.520
There's also a ground
plate that you stand on

00:02:50.520 --> 00:02:53.870
with X3 that creates a ground,

00:02:53.870 --> 00:02:56.940
so if you're doing a dead lift or a squat,

00:02:56.940 --> 00:02:59.120
your ankles are not bending inward.

00:02:59.120 --> 00:03:00.320
Ask a football player

00:03:00.320 --> 00:03:02.490
if the ankle likes lateral force.

00:03:02.490 --> 00:03:03.323
It doesn't.

00:03:04.610 --> 00:03:07.800
We cancel all that out

00:03:07.800 --> 00:03:10.700
with the bar and the plate

00:03:10.700 --> 00:03:13.140
so that joints are straight,

00:03:13.140 --> 00:03:15.540
they're always comfortable,
and you can produce

00:03:15.540 --> 00:03:17.820
the proper levels of force with X3

00:03:17.820 --> 00:03:19.980
to trigger that aggressive
level of growth.

00:03:19.980 --> 00:03:21.410
You wanna learn any more,

00:03:21.410 --> 00:03:24.073
please read the science
page on the website.

